fields.title: Title 2
fields.content:
The Netherlord's Chaotic Wrathsteed is an epic flying mount introduced in the Legion expansion. It is a warlock class mount and can be ridden only by the members of this World of Warcraft class. There are only 12 class mounts in WoW including this one. Buying the Netherlord's Chaotic Wrathsteed carry will not only allow you to get the original warlock class mount but also acquire 3 color tints.

Boost ETA: ~48 hrs.

Warlocks can ride the Netherlord's Chaotic Wrathsteed only after the completion of Class Hall and Broken
Shore meta-achievements. They can still be fulfilled in BFA and shadowlands expansions.

The warlock class mount carry will get you:
start of the boost within 30-50 minutes;
the completed storyline class-hall quest to receive the Netherlord's Chaotic Wrathsteed;


ability to acquire additional color tints for the class mount upon completion of related Power Ascended achievement;
high-class VPN security.

The class mount quest only becomes available after the completion of the Legion major achievements such as a Glorious Campaign and Breaching the Tomb. The additional artifact-related achievement - Power Ascended will unlock the additional color schemes for this awesome flying mount.

The warlock class mount color tints include the following variations:

The original Netherlord's Chaotic Wrathsteed in green color is obtained from a class quest storyline.
Red/orange flame recolor - Hellblazing Reins of the Brimstone Wrathsteed can be purchased from Calydus located at the Artifact Forge for x1000 Order Resources after completing The Wrathsteed of Xoroth and Power Ascended.
Dark purple option - Shadowy Reins of the Accursed Wrathsteed is obtainable from Lord Hel'Nurath on Broken Shore with a 100% drop rate. It can only drop if you have already completed the class mount quest chain.

TEXT CAPACITY UP TO APPROXIMATELY 3000 SYMBOLS

This unique Paladin class mount was introduced in Legion at the same time with the other 11 class mounts making the total count of 12. It is the original paladin steed that has the golden color scheme and suits perfectly for the most common paladin sets. Buying the Highlord's Charger boost will help you to acquire this epic mount to ride in BFA and Shadowlands.
